# By default the external editor is not enabled.
run
key alt+f2
----
-- view:
[40m[37m> [0m[0m[40m[0m[40m[7m [0m[0m[40m[0m[40m                                                                           [0m‚ê§
[90mM-?[0m [90mtoggle key help[0m[90m ‚Ä¢ [0m[90mC-d[0m [90merase/stop[0m[90m ‚Ä¢ [0m[90mC-c[0m [90mclear/cancel[0m[90m ‚Ä¢ [0m[90mM-.[0m [90mhide/show prompt[0müõá

# But it can be enabled explicitly.
run
enable_ext_edit
key alt+f2
----
TEA EXEC
-- view:
[40m[37m> [0m[0m[40m[0m[40m[7m [0m[0m[40m[0m[40m                                                                           [0m‚ê§
[90mM-?[0m [90mtoggle key help[0m[90m ‚Ä¢ [0m[90mC-d[0m [90merase/stop[0m[90m ‚Ä¢ [0m[90mC-c[0m [90mclear/cancel[0m[90m ‚Ä¢ [0m[90mM-.[0m [90mhide/show prompt[0müõá

# However this doesn't work if the env var is unset.
run
unset_editor_env
key alt+f2
----
TEA PRINT: {env var EDITOR empty or not set}
